	  <element name="Volume of Literature" type="Sub Race" source="Sionnach's Mind" id="ID_SUB_RACE_VOLUMEOFLITERATURE">
		<supports>Scriptorii</supports>
		<requirements />
		<description>
		<p>Your core text is a work of masterful fiction, full of high drama, human truths, pathos, sudden reversals, empathy, pain and loss, giving you uncommon insight into other people.</p>
		<p>
			<span class="feature">Ability Score Increase.</span> Your Charisma score increases by 1.<br />
			<span class="feature">Proficiencies.</span> Choose one skill proficiency from Deception, Intimidation, Performance, or Persuasion.<br />
			<span class="feature">Spoil the Ending.</span> You use your knowledge of stories to encourage your allies and deflate your enemies, telling of how similar attempts have succeeded or failed in the past. As an action, you can impose advantage or disadvantage on a creature’s next ability check or attack roll, provided it can hear and understand you. You may use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once). You regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.<br />
		</p>
		</description>
